  "texts": [
    "This raw text is often referred to as unstructured data, as opposed to data in a table or other format ready for analysis.",
    "Many pipelines start with some form of tokenization, which splits text into smaller units, referred to as tokens.",
    "This might be paragraphs into sentences, or phrases into individual words, punctuation, or words into sub-words.",
    "One specific case of tokenization is sentence segmentation which aims to isolate individual sentences.",
    "This can be as simple as splitting at every period, or can employ more complex algorithms [7,8]."
  ],
